<div class="p-4 sm:ml-64">
    <div id="part1" class="p-4 rounded-lg dark:border-gray-700">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-4">
            <div class="p-5 text-center">
                <h5 class="mb-2 text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-btn">200,000 tonnes</h5>
                <br>
                <p class="mb-3 text-xl font-normal text-btn">The amount of clothes thrown away in<br> Australia each year</p>
                <br>
                <h5 class="mb-2 text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-btn">27kg</h5>
                <br>
                <p class="mb-3 text-xl font-normal text-btn">The average amount of clothing that<br> each Australian buys each year</p>

            </div>
            <div class=" dark:bg-gray-800">
                <img class="h-80 pt-8" src="~/Content/images/info-waste-img1.jpg" alt="" />
            </div>

        </div>
        <div class="flex justify-center items-center mx-auto px-60 bg-white rounded-sm items-center dark:bg-gray-800 dark:border-gray-700">
            <img class="object-cover justify-center" src="~/Content/images/info-watste-img2.png" alt="" />
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-center justify-center rounded dark:bg-gray-800">
            <p class="mb-8 text-xl font-normal px-60 text-btn">
                <br><br>
                Australia is the <span class="mb-3 text-2xl font-normal text-CardText">second</span> highest consumer country of clothes and consequentially, textile waste has become a massive contributor to Australia’s waste problem.<br><br>

                Fast Fashion is largely responsible for this. It is a clothing market made up of products which are produced rapidly by mass-market retailers. The purpose of this business model is to allow clothes to be on shelves faster, to keep up with fast developing fashion trends, to allow users to buy more. A downside of this, however, is that the clothes are made using cheap, unsustainable fabric that not only damages the environment but leads to poorer quality clothes which have shorter life spans. It is because of this, that our clothing waste problem is only worsening as Australians are buying on average 60% more clothing than 15 years ago, and only keeping them for half as long.
                <br><br>
            </p>
        </div>

    </div>
    <div id="part2" class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-4 mb-40 justify-center items-center">
        <div class="col-start-2 col-span-5 px-20 text-center">
            <h5 class="mb-2 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-btn"> What is Fashion Sustainability?</h5>
            <br>
            <p class="text-xl font-normal text-CardText text-left">
                Sustainability in fashion production and
                consumption is crucial in helping reduce Australia’s waste problem.
                Its about making clothes in a way which is kinder to the environment, people and our health.
                This way, you can buy from your favourite clothing brands and rest easy that they aren’t damaging the planet unnecessarily or treating their workers unfairly. 
                By choosing sustainable fashion, you can do your bit to support an eco-friendly revolution of the fashion industry.
                Plus, sustainable clothing is made from more durable fabrics meaning your new favourite dress will have a significantly longer lifespan!
                You are not just helping the planet, but also helping you save money as you don’t have to go and rebuy after a few wears.
                When wearing sustainable fashion, you can not only look good, but help our planet feel good!
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-start-7 col-span-6">
            <div class="image-container">
                <img class="object-scale-down" src="~/Content/images/info-img3.jpg" alt="" />
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="image-container">

        </div>
    </div>
